Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1)	Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2)	Mental health evaluation and follow through;
3)	No contact with the Casper family;
4)	No contact with Kiel police officers or their families unless in a professional capacity;
5)	Pay court costs;
6)	Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7)	Provide a DNA sample
8)	Twenty (20) days in the county jail, under the Huber law, to commence 06-02-2017 by 5:00 p.m.
9)	Additional forty (40) days jail, under the Huber law stayed, to be imposed upon the agents discretion and upon order of the court. (Jail on count 4 only)
Minutes.

Order to Modify Bond.
The Court now orders:
1) defendant shall not travel outside of Manitowoc County;
2) if the defendant is living in Sheboygan COunty, he may travel to Sheboygan County;
3) if the defendant needs to travel outside of Manitowoc County for business, he must present the State and the Court with the name and address of the business he needs to travel to.  He must also provide the State and the Court with the time frame needed for the travel.  The Court will then amend the bond to allow for that specific travel;
4) if the defendant wishes to travel outside Manitowoc County to visit his ailing friend, he must present to the State and to the court the name and address of the friend and the desired time frame for the travel.  The Court will then amend the bond to allow for that specific travel.
Copy to jail.
